      <itunes:author>Aengus Anderson and Micah Saul</itunes:author>
      <itunes:summary>Jan Lundberg is a former oil industry analyst turned environmental activist. He is the founder of Culture Change and the Sail Transport Network. We spoke to him about peak oil, the tension between individualism and community, the innate value of nature, and the difficulty of compromise. He provides an interesting counterpoint to Dr. Max More and approaches environmentalism from a drastically different perspective than Peter Warren.  Learn more at www.findtheconversation.com</itunes:summary>
      <itunes:image href="http://www.findtheconversation.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/jan-470x260.jpg"/>
